caption: I’ve gone to this Starbucks a crazy number of times. I went when GW was in person and online. And I have to say the service is horrible. During in person, it would take at least 20 minutes to get my order even with mobile orders. Now that we’re online, this place is usually pretty empty. I like to use mobile order so whenever I walk in they just completely ignore me. The staff are always gossiping and they never pay attention to their customers. They would always have my order ready on the counter but I cant ever get it because the staff ignore me completely. It takes at least 8 minutes for them to notice that I’m waiting for my order. I find that some staff are pretty mean too. There’s only like one or two people that are really nice and welcoming.

I can't figure out why this Starbucks only has three stars. It was fast, friendly, even was serenaded while our order was being cooked. And the impossible breakfast sandwich, well, impossibly delicious.

Super busy and not enough seating. Our coffees were forgotten so I had to ask for them. Finally got replacement ones and they were wrong size and tasted like burned water. Bagels were fine but they didn’t include the butter. Also had to ask for that. Won’t be back.

I stopped by today and it was the second time in a week that I came in here with the hopes of getting some work completed.  The reason why I came here was because the library next door was closed. It seems like they have a thing for keeping the music loud like a concert hall!!  I've often wondered why they keep the music loud, because I'm sure it's not appealing for most people.  The good thing about this location is that it is clean and they seem to have more comfortable seating than other places. Finding a sest on the other hand can sometimes be a challenge depending on the time of day. Today I ordered a regular grande coffee, and it tasted alright. The service was adequate and it was fast. The hours here are not always consistent, and they may be different depending on the schedule of the university. Everything else about this place is great, I just wish that someday they make it more relaxing and quiet.

I visit this Starbucks daily, and yes the wait is very long because it's on a college campus; however, my experience this morning was different than any other. I have been an advocate for individuals with Autism for years now and immediately noticed that there was a customer who was high functioning but non-verbal. He was growing impatient with the long wait, which was about 25 minutes to get a drink. I went up to him and asked him what his name is and what his order was, and he showed me his phone (it was a mobile order). I asked the barista if he had the order ready, and he said it was being made right then. About 2 minutes later, the man got his drink and thanked me with a smile and a handshake. About 2 more minutes later, he came back into the Starbucks and walked over to me and pointed at the sticker on the cup. He was pointing to the word "warm". I asked him if the drink was too hot, and he nodded. I got the attention of the barista again, and the man pointed to the sticker again to show him. AWithout any hesitation or questions, the barista swiftly remade the drink for him at the right temperature. The man was so grateful and shook the barista's hand and walked out of Starbucks with the largest smile as he drank his hot chocolate. I am amazed with the barista's ability to work in a situation where he has people yelling at him all morning for their order taking so long when the store is at maximum capacity and still have the temperament to handle a situation requiring his patience and kindness with an Autistic individual. This barista's actions are how every barista or server should respond to such an instance, but that often isn't the case. I don't think I can ever really complain about the wait again after this.

I've gone to this Starbucks 2-3 a week for the past three months.  I'll never go again.  It's always crowded but the staff manage.  I've always just ordered a large no frills coffee and service was always timely.  Today I opted for a change and ordered a danish.  After a 10+ minute wait I went back through the line to find out that there was a miscommunication and the pastry was never given out.  The manager was unapologetic, said that it happens, and gave me a refund when I asked her if this was normal.  After staring at her for a few more seconds she asked me what I wanted and when I said I wanted an apology she rolled her eyes and said she was sorry.  All in all if you just want black coffee this is a great place but it seems if you want anything else expect a wait and for it to be screwed up by an overworked staff that doesn't care.

The calming coffee shop atmosphere Starbucks is supposed to represent is  substituted for what feels like a trashy lounge. I am only able to get studying done by putting on a white noise generator. I get that this chain probably doesn't want people staying for hours, but that is not a realistic expectation given that the Starbucks serves a University. LOWER THE VOLUME - I'm trying to get some actual studying done. And so are 4 other people sitting near me at this moment.

They decided instead of cups and sugars in the side carrier they would include two grande cups full of half and half. One of which didn't have a tightened lid, so that spilled as soon as I picked it up. And the weight made the side carrier totally useless. Grabbed my own sugar and stirrers, fine. Asked for some cups from the barista so we could, you know, drink the coffee. The barista informed me that instead of taking two steps to the left and grabbing me cups, I would have to ask the cashier. Yes, I ordered and paid online, but I had to wait 5 minutes in line to acquire 6 empty cups.

This has to be one of my favorite Starbucks in the area.  Despite the political atmosphere, the people there are always friendly, even when it appears to be busy.  When there is a line in the morning, it tends to move fast.  The condiments area is always stocked with milk and sugar, and the bathrooms seem to be in good shape!  Also, I've never had any problem finding a seat inside.  Usually my thing is just regular coffee, so I'm not too keen about late and mocha drinks that they serve up.  Sometimes I do need the Cafe Frapacinno fix to get me through a hot summer's day.  All-in-all I like chilling there and I do manage to get Facebook work accomplished.
